gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Trail Blazers 128, Raptors 118
gameRecap.excerpt: Portland defeats Toronto in OT, 128-118. For Portland, DeAndre Ayton led the way with a season-high 30 points, 19 rebounds, and two steals while aided by Dalano Banton (25 points (five 3PM), seven rebounds, four assists) and Anfernee Simons (23 points (four 3PM), four rebounds, seven assists) in the victory. Immanuel Quickley finished with 28 points (four 3PM) and seven assists with Gary Trent Jr. adding 23 point, five rebounds, three assists, and two steals for the Raptors in the losing effort. Portland improves to 18-45, while Toronto moves to 23-41 in the loss.
